e(figsize=(4, 3), facecolor='w')\n","plt.plot(x, ys, '-')\n","plt.fill_between(x, ys, 195, where=(ys > 195), facecolor='g', alpha=0.6)\n","plt.title(\"Sample Visualization\", fontsize=10)\n","\n","data = io.BytesIO()\n","plt.savefig(data)\n","image = F\"data:image/png;base64,{base64.b64encode(data.getvalue()).decode()}\"\n","alt = \"Sample Visualization\"\n","display.display(display.Markdown(F\"\"\"![{alt}]({image})\"\"\"))\n","plt.close(fig)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"5bf4b7a2"},"source":["## 1. Data Acquisition\n","\n","To build a market risk dashboard, we first need financial data. We'll start by fetching historical stock prices. `yfinance` is a popular and easy-to-use library for downloading historical market data from Yahoo! Finance."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"6e07e5a6","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128634,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":4102,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"ad68514d-576b-4f3b-8506-4f1e75c2aaba"},"source":["pip install yfinance pandas"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Requirement already satisfied: yfinance in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (0.2.66)\n","Requirement already satisfied: pandas in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (2.2.2)\n","Requirement already satisfied: numpy>=1.16.5 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (2.0.2)\n","Requirement already satisfied: requests>=2.31 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (2.32.4)\n","Requirement already satisfied: multitasking>=0.0.7 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (0.0.13)\n","Requirement already satisfied: platformdirs>=2.0.0 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (4.10.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: pytz>=2022.5 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (2025.2)\n","Requirement already satisfied: frozendict>=2.3.4 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (2.4.7)\n","Requirement already satisfied: peewee>=3.16.2 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (4.1.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: beautifulsoup4>=4.11.1 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (4.13.5)\n","Requirement already satisfied: curl_cffi>=0.7 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (0.15.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: protobuf>=3.19.0 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (5.29.6)\n","Requirement already satisfied: websockets>=13.0 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from yfinance) (15.0.1)\n","Requirement already satisfied: python-dateutil>=2.8.2 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from pandas) (2.9.0.post0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: tzdata>=2022.7 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from pandas) (2026.2)\n","Requirement already satisfied: soupsieve>1.2 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from beautifulsoup4>=4.11.1->yfinance) (2.8.4)\n","Requirement already satisfied: typing-extensions>=4.0.0 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from beautifulsoup4>=4.11.1->yfinance) (4.15.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: cffi>=2.0.0 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from curl_cffi>=0.7->yfinance) (2.0.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: certifi>=2024.2.2 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from curl_cffi>=0.7->yfinance) (2026.6.17)\n","Requirement already satisfied: rich in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from curl_cffi>=0.7->yfinance) (13.9.4)\n","Requirement already satisfied: six>=1.5 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from python-dateutil>=2.8.2->pandas) (1.17.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: charset_normalizer<4,>=2 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from requests>=2.31->yfinance) (3.4.7)\n","Requirement already satisfied: idna<4,>=2.5 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from requests>=2.31->yfinance) (3.18)\n","Requirement already satisfied: urllib3<3,>=1.21.1 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from requests>=2.31->yfinance) (2.5.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: pycparser in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from cffi>=2.0.0->curl_cffi>=0.7->yfinance) (3.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: markdown-it-py>=2.2.0 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from rich->curl_cffi>=0.7->yfinance) (4.2.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: pygments<3.0.0,>=2.13.0 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from rich->curl_cffi>=0.7->yfinance) (2.20.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: mdurl~=0.1 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from markdown-it-py>=2.2.0->rich->curl_cffi>=0.7->yfinance) (0.1.2)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"1470f820"},"source":["Now that we have `yfinance` and `pandas` installed, we can download historical stock data. Let's get data for a few common market indices or stocks. You can replace these with the assets you want to analyze.\n","\n","For example, we'll fetch data for SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust (SPY), Invesco QQQ Trust (QQQ), and iShares Russell 2000 ETF (IWM) for the last 5 years."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"df086ec0","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128688,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":24,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"b9a7993c-95be-41f1-90cc-d8fdc6e4c8d5"},"source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","\n","tickers = ['SPY', 'QQQ', 'IWM']\n","# Use auto_adjust=True to get only adjusted closing prices directly\n","# and actions=False to avoid dividend/split info which creates extra columns\n","data = yf.download(tickers, start='2019-01-01', end='2024-01-01', auto_adjust=True, actions=False)\n","\n","# The DataFrame 'data' now directly contains the adjusted close prices for each ticker\n","closing_prices = data['Close'] # 'Close' column now contains the adjusted close prices\n","\n","print(\"Shape of the downloaded data:\", closing_prices.shape)\n","print(closing_prices.head())"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["[*********************100%***********************]  3 of 3 completed"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Shape of the downloaded data: (1258, 3)\n","Ticker             IWM         QQQ         SPY\n","Date                                          \n","2019-01-02  122.686043  147.878342  223.805939\n","2019-01-03  120.490356  143.047104  218.465302\n","2019-01-04  124.991112  149.167297  225.782990\n","2019-01-07  127.177704  150.943192  227.563187\n","2019-01-08  129.127441  152.308548  229.701233\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"f5c8c4d9"},"source":["## 2. Calculate Daily Returns\n","\n","Daily returns are a crucial input for most market risk calculations. We can calculate them from the adjusted closing prices using the percentage change method."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"fcbf0633","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128710,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":19,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"3cb3f1b1-7ef2-459a-a2c8-f97ef1877d88"},"source":["# Calculate daily returns\n","daily_returns = closing_prices.pct_change().dropna()\n","\n","print(\"Shape of the daily returns data:\", daily_returns.shape)\n","print(daily_returns.head())"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Shape of the daily returns data: (1257, 3)\n","Ticker           IWM       QQQ       SPY\n","Date                                    \n","2019-01-03 -0.017897 -0.032670 -0.023863\n","2019-01-04  0.037354  0.042784  0.033496\n","2019-01-07  0.017494  0.011905  0.007885\n","2019-01-08  0.015331  0.009045  0.009395\n","2019-01-09  0.008255  0.008150  0.004674\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"faeb5aad"},"source":["## 3. Calculate Volatility\n","\n","Volatility is a measure of the dispersion of returns for a given security or market index. It is often calculated as the standard deviation of returns. For market risk, we typically annualize the daily volatility."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"db90417d","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128729,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":17,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"79dfdd97-a3b7-4859-b213-d106a921f9a0"},"source":["# Calculate daily standard deviation (volatility)\n","daily_volatility = daily_returns.std()\n","\n","# Annualize volatility (assuming 252 trading days in a year)\n","annualized_volatility = daily_volatility * (252**0.5)\n","\n","print(\"Daily Volatility:\")\n","print(daily_volatility)\n","print(\"\\nAnnualized Volatility:\")\n","print(annualized_volatility)\n","\n","# Display as percentage\n","print(\"\\nAnnualized Volatility (%):\")\n","print((annualized_volatility * 100).round(2))"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Daily Volatility:\n","Ticker\n","IWM    0.016834\n","QQQ    0.016011\n","SPY    0.013226\n","dtype: float64\n","\n","Annualized Volatility:\n","Ticker\n","IWM    0.267225\n","QQQ    0.254165\n","SPY    0.209957\n","dtype: float64\n","\n","Annualized Volatility (%):\n","Ticker\n","IWM    26.72\n","QQQ    25.42\n","SPY    21.00\n","dtype: float64\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"7b5ded35"},"source":["## 4. Calculate Value at Risk (VaR)\n","\n","Value at Risk (VaR) is a measure of the maximum potential loss that could be incurred over a specified period of time with a given level of confidence. We'll calculate historical VaR, which directly uses past returns to estimate future risk.\n","\n","Let's calculate 1-day VaR at 95% and 99% confidence levels."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"78eedb79","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128745,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":13,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"d6866396-625e-4b07-b926-e76f8f3127e9"},"source":["import numpy as np\n","\n","# Define confidence levels\n","confidence_level_95 = 0.05 # For 95% VaR, we look at the 5th percentile\n","confidence_level_99 = 0.01 # For 99% VaR, we look at the 1st percentile\n","\n","# Calculate historical VaR\n","# VaR is typically expressed as a positive number representing loss\n","VaR_95 = daily_returns.quantile(confidence_level_95)\n","VaR_99 = daily_returns.quantile(confidence_level_99)\n","\n","print(\"1-day Historical VaR (95% confidence):\")\n","print(VaR_95)\n","print(\"\\n1-day Historical VaR (99% confidence):\")\n","print(VaR_99)\n","\n","# Display VaR as percentage\n","print(\"\\n1-day Historical VaR (95% confidence, %):\")\n","print((VaR_95 * 100).round(2))\n","print(\"\\n1-day Historical VaR (99% confidence, %):\")\n","print((VaR_99 * 100).round(2))"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["1-day Historical VaR (95% confidence):\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -0.025108\n","QQQ   -0.025635\n","SPY   -0.019288\n","Name: 0.05, dtype: float64\n","\n","1-day Historical VaR (99% confidence):\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -0.039364\n","QQQ   -0.042958\n","SPY   -0.036165\n","Name: 0.01, dtype: float64\n","\n","1-day Historical VaR (95% confidence, %):\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -2.51\n","QQQ   -2.56\n","SPY   -1.93\n","Name: 0.05, dtype: float64\n","\n","1-day Historical VaR (99% confidence, %):\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -3.94\n","QQQ   -4.30\n","SPY   -3.62\n","Name: 0.01, dtype: float64\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"4d0eebf7"},"source":["## 5. Calculate Expected Shortfall (ES)\n","\n","Expected Shortfall (ES), also known as Conditional VaR (CVaR), is a risk measure that quantifies the expected value of losses that exceed the Value at Risk (VaR). It gives a more conservative estimate of risk than VaR because it takes into account the severity of losses in the tail of the distribution.\n","\n","Let's calculate 1-day ES at 95% and 99% confidence levels."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"344e9a00","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128761,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":14,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"f9ec3666-4a2a-4610-81bf-29ea9aa71371"},"source":["# Calculate Expected Shortfall (ES)\n","# ES for a given confidence level is the average of returns that are worse than the VaR at that level.\n","\n","# Ensure VaR is already calculated from previous steps\n","# For 95% ES, we consider returns below the 5th percentile (VaR_95)\n","# For 99% ES, we consider returns below the 1st percentile (VaR_99)\n","\n","ES_95 = daily_returns[daily_returns < VaR_95].mean()\n","ES_99 = daily_returns[daily_returns < VaR_99].mean()\n","\n","print(\"1-day Historical Expected Shortfall (95% confidence):\")\n","print(ES_95)\n","print(\"\\n1-day Historical Expected Shortfall (99% confidence):\")\n","print(ES_99)\n","\n","# Display ES as percentage\n","print(\"\\n1-day Historical Expected Shortfall (95% confidence, %):\")\n","print((ES_95 * 100).round(2))\n","print(\"\\n1-day Historical Expected Shortfall (99% confidence, %):\")\n","print((ES_99 * 100).round(2))"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["1-day Historical Expected Shortfall (95% confidence):\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -0.038637\n","QQQ   -0.037684\n","SPY   -0.032151\n","dtype: float64\n","\n","1-day Historical Expected Shortfall (99% confidence):\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -0.067872\n","QQQ   -0.059129\n","SPY   -0.056304\n","dtype: float64\n","\n","1-day Historical Expected Shortfall (95% confidence, %):\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -3.86\n","QQQ   -3.77\n","SPY   -3.22\n","dtype: float64\n","\n","1-day Historical Expected Shortfall (99% confidence, %):\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -6.79\n","QQQ   -5.91\n","SPY   -5.63\n","dtype: float64\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"8b09051d"},"source":["## 6. Calculate Correlation\n","\n","Correlation measures the degree to which two assets move in relation to each other. A positive correlation means assets tend to move in the same direction, while a negative correlation means they tend to move in opposite directions. This is essential for portfolio diversification."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":668},"id":"3bf3b101","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128809,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":18,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"bd9897fb-183c-4ca3-9717-fe5222702a20"},"source":["# Calculate the correlation matrix of daily returns\n","correlation_matrix = daily_returns.corr()\n","\n","print(\"Correlation Matrix of Daily Returns:\")\n","print(correlation_matrix)\n","\n","# Optional: Visualize the correlation matrix using a heatmap\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n","sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt=\".2f\")\n","plt.title('Correlation Matrix of Asset Daily Returns')\n","plt.show()"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Correlation Matrix of Daily Returns:\n","Ticker       IWM       QQQ       SPY\n","Ticker                              \n","IWM     1.000000  0.773321  0.880089\n","QQQ     0.773321  1.000000  0.931452\n","SPY     0.880089  0.931452  1.000000\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x600 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"70146aa1"},"source":["## 7. Calculate Drawdown\n","\n","Drawdown is the peak-to-trough decline during a specific period for an investment, trading account, or fund. A drawdown is usually quoted as a percentage, from the peak amount to the trough amount. It is an indicator of risk.\n","\n","We will calculate the maximum drawdown for each asset."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":687},"id":"3e35bcc4","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128940,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":125,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"469a25a4-dc60-43d1-93ca-e981a704ee43"},"source":["# Calculate cumulative returns\n","cumulative_returns = (1 + daily_returns).cumprod()\n","\n","# Calculate peaks\n","# The 'expanding()' window takes all data from the beginning up to the current point\n","peaks = cumulative_returns.expanding(min_periods=1).max()\n","\n","# Calculate drawdowns\n","drawdowns = (cumulative_returns / peaks) - 1\n","\n","# Calculate maximum drawdown for each asset\n","max_drawdowns = drawdowns.min()\n","\n","print(\"Maximum Drawdowns:\")\n","print(max_drawdowns)\n","\n","# Display maximum drawdowns as percentage\n","print(\"\\nMaximum Drawdowns (%):\")\n","print((max_drawdowns * 100).round(2))\n","\n","# Optional: Plot the drawdowns for a visual representation\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n","drawdowns.plot(title='Asset Drawdowns Over Time')\n","plt.xlabel('Date')\n","plt.ylabel('Drawdown')\n","plt.grid(True)\n","plt.show()"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Maximum Drawdowns:\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -0.410724\n","QQQ   -0.351187\n","SPY   -0.337173\n","dtype: float64\n","\n","Maximum Drawdowns (%):\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -41.07\n","QQQ   -35.12\n","SPY   -33.72\n","dtype: float64\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x600 with 0 Axes>"]},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"141a8cda"},"source":["## 8. Stress Testing\n","\n","Stress testing involves evaluating the potential impact of extreme but plausible market events on an investment or portfolio. It helps to understand how robust an investment is under adverse scenarios.\n","\n","For this simple stress test, we will simulate a scenario where daily returns drop by a significant amount (e.g., a 3-standard-deviation shock) across all assets and observe the hypothetical loss."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"0b190497","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128972,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":10,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"9ccbd38e-5d81-4ce9-9155-bc983d89a776"},"source":["# Define the stress scenario: a 3-standard-deviation drop in daily returns\n","# We'll use the average of the historical daily standard deviations across the assets as a general market shock.\n","\n","market_wide_daily_std = daily_returns.std().mean() # Average daily std across assets\n","stress_shock = -3 * market_wide_daily_std # A 3-sigma negative shock\n","\n","print(f\"Simulated daily return shock: {stress_shock:.4f} or {stress_shock * 100:.2f}%\")\n","\n","# Apply the shock to the last available closing prices\n","# This is a simplified approach; in a full model, you might apply this to the full return series,\n","# or simulate multiple scenarios.\n","\n","last_closing_prices = closing_prices.iloc[-1]\n","\n","# Calculate hypothetical returns under stress\n","stress_returns = daily_returns.iloc[-1] + stress_shock\n","\n","# Calculate hypothetical prices under stress\n","stress_prices = last_closing_prices * (1 + stress_returns)\n","\n","print(\"\\nLast Closing Prices:\")\n","print(last_closing_prices)\n","\n","print(\"\\nHypothetical Returns under Stress:\")\n","print(stress_returns)\n","\n","print(\"\\nHypothetical Prices under Stress:\")\n","print(stress_prices)\n","\n","# Calculate the hypothetical loss from the last closing price\n","hypothetical_loss_value = last_closing_prices - stress_prices\n","hypothetical_loss_percentage = (hypothetical_loss_value / last_closing_prices) * 100\n","\n","print(\"\\nHypothetical Loss (Value) under Stress:\")\n","print(hypothetical_loss_value)\n","\n","print(\"\\nHypothetical Loss (Percentage) under Stress:\")\n","print(hypothetical_loss_percentage.round(2))"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Simulated daily return shock: -0.0461 or -4.61%\n","\n","Last Closing Prices:\n","Ticker\n","IWM    195.357407\n","QQQ    404.092346\n","SPY    461.391296\n","Name: 2023-12-29 00:00:00, dtype: float64\n","\n","Hypothetical Returns under Stress:\n","Ticker\n","IWM   -0.062391\n","QQQ   -0.050398\n","SPY   -0.048965\n","Name: 2023-12-29 00:00:00, dtype: float64\n","\n","Hypothetical Prices under Stress:\n","Ticker\n","IWM    183.168922\n","QQQ    383.726798\n","SPY    438.799042\n","Name: 2023-12-29 00:00:00, dtype: float64\n","\n","Hypothetical Loss (Value) under Stress:\n","Ticker\n","IWM    12.188484\n","QQQ    20.365549\n","SPY    22.592255\n","Name: 2023-12-29 00:00:00, dtype: float64\n","\n","Hypothetical Loss (Percentage) under Stress:\n","Ticker\n","IWM    6.24\n","QQQ    5.04\n","SPY    4.90\n","Name: 2023-12-29 00:00:00, dtype: float64\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"873c5b50","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098128993,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":18,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"601ecb2c-22b4-4bed-98d6-bd72693e8b4d"},"source":["%%writefile risk_dashboard.py\n","\n","import streamlit as st\n","import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns\n","\n","st.set_page_config(layout=\"wide\")\n","\n","st.title(\"Market Risk Dashboard\")\n","\n","# --- Sidebar for User Inputs ---\n","st.sidebar.header(\"Configuration\")\n","\n","# Asset selection\n","default_tickers = ['SPY', 'QQQ', 'IWM', 'AAPL', 'MSFT']\n","tickers_input = st.sidebar.text_input(\n","    \"Enter Ticker Symbols (comma-separated):\",\n","    value=\", \".join(default_tickers)\n",")\n","selected_tickers = [ticker.strip().upper() for ticker in tickers_input.split(',') if ticker.strip()]\n","\n","# Date Range\n","start_date = st.sidebar.date_input(\"Start Date\", value=pd.to_datetime('2019-01-01'))\n","end_date = st.sidebar.date_input(\"End Date\", value=pd.to_datetime('2024-01-01'))\n","\n","# Confidence Levels for VaR/ES\n","confidence_level_var = st.sidebar.slider(\"VaR/ES Confidence Level (%)\", 90, 99, 95)\n","alpha_var = (100 - confidence_level_var) / 100\n","\n","st.sidebar.markdown(\"---\")\n","st.sidebar.markdown(\"**Note**: Data is fetched from Yahoo Finance. Ensure tickers are valid.\")\n","\n","# --- Data Acquisition ---\n","@st.cache_data\n","def get_historical_data(tickers, start, end):\n","    if not tickers:\n","        return pd.DataFrame() # Return empty DataFrame if no tickers\n","    data = yf.download(tickers, start=start, end=end, auto_adjust=True, actions=False)\n","    if 'Close' in data.columns:\n","        return data['Close']\n","    else: # Handle single ticker case where 'Close' might be a direct column\n","        return data # Assuming it's already the closing prices\n","\n","closing_prices = get_historical_data(selected_tickers, start_date, end_date)\n","\n","if closing_prices.empty or closing_prices.isnull().all().all():\n","    st.error(\"No data available for the selected tickers/date range. Please check your inputs.\")\n","    st.stop()\n","\n","st.subheader(\"1. Historical Closing Prices\")\n","st.write(\"First 5 rows of Adjusted Closing Prices:\")\n","st.dataframe(closing_prices.head())\n","\n","# --- Daily Returns ---\n","st.subheader(\"2. Daily Returns\")\n","daily_returns = closing_prices.pct_change().dropna()\n","st.write(\"First 5 rows of Daily Returns:\")\n","st.dataframe(daily_returns.head())\n","\n","# --- Volatility ---\n","st.subheader(\"3. Volatility\")\n","daily_volatility = daily_returns.std()\n","annualized_volatility = daily_volatility * (np.sqrt(252)) # Assuming 252 trading days\n","\n","volatility_df = pd.DataFrame({\n","    'Daily Volatility': daily_volatility,\n","    'Annualized Volatility': annualized_volatility,\n","    'Annualized Volatility (%)': (annualized_volatility * 100).round(2)\n","})\n","st.dataframe(volatility_df)\n","\n","# --- Value at Risk (VaR) ---\n","st.subheader(\"4. Value at Risk (VaR)\")\n","VaR = daily_returns.quantile(alpha_var)\n","VaR_df = pd.DataFrame({\n","    f'1-day VaR ({confidence_level_var}%)': VaR,\n","    f'1-day VaR ({confidence_level_var}%) (%)': (VaR * 100).round(2)\n","})\n","st.dataframe(VaR_df)\n","\n","# --- Expected Shortfall (ES) ---\n","st.subheader(\"5. Expected Shortfall (ES)\")\n","ES = daily_returns[daily_returns < VaR].mean()\n","ES_df = pd.DataFrame({\n","    f'1-day ES ({confidence_level_var}%)': ES,\n","    f'1-day ES ({confidence_level_var}%) (%)': (ES * 100).round(2)\n","})\n","st.dataframe(ES_df)\n","\n","# --- Correlation ---\n","st.subheader(\"6. Correlation Matrix\")\n","correlation_matrix = daily_returns.corr()\n","st.dataframe(correlation_matrix)\n","\n","fig_corr, ax_corr = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))\n","sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt=\".2f\", ax=ax_corr)\n","ax_corr.set_title('Correlation Matrix of Asset Daily Returns')\n","st.pyplot(fig_corr)\n","\n","# --- Drawdown ---\n","st.subheader(\"7. Drawdown\")\n","cumulative_returns = (1 + daily_returns).cumprod()\n","peaks = cumulative_returns.expanding(min_periods=1).max()\n","drawdowns = (cumulative_returns / peaks) - 1\n","max_drawdowns = drawdowns.min()\n","\n","drawdown_df = pd.DataFrame({\n","    'Maximum Drawdown': max_drawdowns,\n","    'Maximum Drawdown (%)': (max_drawdowns * 100).round(2)\n","})\n","st.dataframe(drawdown_df)\n","\n","fig_drawdown, ax_drawdown = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))\n","drawdowns.plot(title='Asset Drawdowns Over Time', ax=ax_drawdown)\n","ax_drawdown.set_xlabel('Date')\n","ax_drawdown.set_ylabel('Drawdown')\n","ax_drawdown.grid(True)\n","st.pyplot(fig_drawdown)\n","\n","# --- Stress Testing ---\n","st.subheader(\"8. Stress Testing\")\n","st.write(\"Simulating a 3-standard-deviation shock to daily returns.\")\n","\n","market_wide_daily_std = daily_returns.std().mean()\n","stress_shock = -3 * market_wide_daily_std\n","\n","st.write(f\"Simulated daily return shock: {stress_shock:.4f} or {stress_shock * 100:.2f}%\")\n","\n","last_closing_prices = closing_prices.iloc[-1]\n","stress_returns = daily_returns.iloc[-1] + stress_shock\n","stress_prices = last_closing_prices * (1 + stress_returns)\n","\n","hypothetical_loss_value = last_closing_prices - stress_prices\n","hypothetical_loss_percentage = (hypothetical_loss_value / last_closing_prices) * 100\n","\n","stress_test_df = pd.DataFrame({\n","    'Last Closing Price': last_closing_prices,\n","    'Hypothetical Return under Stress': stress_returns,\n","    'Hypothetical Price under Stress': stress_prices,\n","    'Hypothetical Loss (Value)': hypothetical_loss_value,\n","    'Hypothetical Loss (%)': hypothetical_loss_percentage.round(2)\n","})\n","st.dataframe(stress_test_df)\n","\n","st.markdown(\"---\")\n","st.info(\"This dashboard provides a basic overview of market risk metrics. For production use, consider more advanced models and validation.\")"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Overwriting risk_dashboard.py\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"376e9881","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783098135701,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":6713,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"118080b0-7c55-443f-adfd-b706b0acfade"},"source":["%%bash\n","pip install streamlit pyngrok yfinance pandas matplotlib seaborn numpy\n","pip freeze > requirements.txt"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Requirement already satisfied: streamlit in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (1.58.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: pyngrok in /usr